{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox person | name = Anthony Atamanuik | image = Anthony Atamanuik by Gage Skidmore.jpg | caption = [[Politicon]] 2016<ref name="politicon.com">{{cite web|url=https://politicon.com/speaker/anthony-atamanuik/|title=» Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=politicon.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|6|15}} | birth_place = | occupation = Comedian, actor and writer | years_active = 1997–present | alma_mater = [[Emerson College]]<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://ucbtourco.com/talent/1603|title=Cast Member - Anthony Atamanuik|first=|last=Upright Citizens Brigade|date=|website=UCB TourCo|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> | website = }}
'''Anthony Atamanuik''' {{IPAc-en|ə|ˈ|t|æ|m|ə|n|ɪ|k}}<ref>Name pronounced by person himself, {{cite web|url=https://veggiekarma.com/anthony-atamanuik-auditions-for-countess-luann-in-real-housewives-the-movie-wwhl/|title=Anthony Atamanuik Auditions for Countess LuAnn in 'Real Housewives the Movie|date=September 4, 2015}}</ref> (born June 15, 1974) is a writer,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vimeo.com/user994528|title=Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=Vimeo|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> actor,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/AbsoluteAnthony/|title=Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=facebook.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> and comedian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.earwolf.com/person/anthony-atamanuik/|title=Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=Earwolf|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> Atamanuik is known primarily for his impersonation of U.S. President [[Donald Trump]], during the campaign and his presidency, first on the [[Trump vs. Bernie]] debate tour and then on ''[[The President Show]]''.
==Early life== Atamanuik was born to Marlene J. Yannetti,<ref>https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:K4F8-PQN</ref><ref>https://www.familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:FLD4-8H5</ref> an actress, choreographer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.emerson.edu/academics/faculty-guide/profile/marlena-yannetti/369|title=Marlena Yannetti - Faculty - Emerson College|website=Emerson College}}</ref> and dancer of Italian<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2017/11/29/567215478/stars-of-the-president-show-present-an-off-the-rails-version-of-trump|title=Stars Of 'The President Show' Present An 'Off The Rails' Version Of Trump|publisher=}}</ref> and [[Ashkenazi]] ancestry, with credits including ''[[How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying (musical)]]'' and Lawrence Peter Atamanuik, a drummer of Ukrainian ancestry, with credits including [[Seatrain (band)|Seatrain]] and [[Alison Krauss]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pearldrum.com/artists/drumset-artists/larry-atamanuik|title=Larry Atamanuik - Pearl Drums|website=pearldrum.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:Bs-oTyKFlRgJ:https://ontarioancestors.org/ogspi_pages/2003/03fra001.htm|title=FRA Surnames 2003 Obituary|website=webcache.googleusercontent.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gettyimages.com/photos/larry-atamanuik|title=Larry Atamanuik Stock Photos and Pictures - Getty Images|website=www.gettyimages.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/465813-Larry-Atamanuik|title=Larry Atamanuik|website=Discogs}}</ref>
==Career== In 1997, Atamanuik graduated with a [[bachelor of science]] in film theory from [[Emerson College]]. He moved to Los Angeles and worked for [[Jim Henson Interactive]], ''[[Mr. Show]]'', and [[Suzanne Somers]]. He moved to New York in 2000. In 2002 he began training and performing at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade]].<ref name="auto"/> Atamanuik appeared in the shorts ''My Wife,'' ''The Ghost'', and ''The Incredible Drunk.''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.howardstern.com/show/2017/5/17/master-trump-impressionist-anthony-atamanuik-talks-new-tv-show-and-huge-tip-howard-left-him-during-his-table-waiting-days/|title=Master Trump Impressionist Anthony Atamanuik Talks New TV Show and the Huge Tip Howard Left Him During His Table-Waiting Days|author=|date=|website=Howard Stern|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/youmadeitweird/anthony-atamanuik|title=Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=soundcloud.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nerdist.com/you-made-it-weird-374-anthony-atamanuik/|title=You Made It Weird #374: Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=July 12, 2017|website= Nerdist.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://youmadeitweird.nerdistind.libsynpro.com/anthony-atamanuik|title=You Made It Weird with Pete Holmes #374: Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=libsynpro.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> He is a member of the improv team Death by Roo Roo and as a co-host on ASSSSCAT3000 and The Tony Show With Anthony Atamanuik<ref>{{cite web|url=https://east.ucbtheatre.com/show/3355|title=The Tony Show With Anthony Atamanuik|author=|date=|website=UCB Theatre|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> and wrote for Time Traveling Bong.<ref name="politicon.com"/>
On television, he appeared in Brett Gelman's ''[[Dinner with Friends with Brett Gelman and Friends#Sequels|Dinner in America]]'' (2016), ''[[30 Rock]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/the-president-show-donald-trump-anthony-atamanuik-interview|title='The President Show' Host on Trying to Make Trump Funny & Alec Baldwin's 'SNL' Take|first=Sean|last=Fitz-Gerald|date=August 14, 2017|website=thrillist.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/04/26/trump-impersonator-anthony-atamanuik-i-don-t-know-why-alec-baldwin-hates-me|title=Trump Impersonator Anthony Atamanuik: I Don’t Know Why Alec Baldwin HateTs Me|first=Matt|last=Wilstein|date=April 26, 2017|website=The Daily Beast|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/anthony-atamanuik-alec-baldwin-donald-trump-feud-2017-5|title=Trump impersonator Anthony Atamanuik opens up about his 'harsh' feud with Alec Baldwin|author=|date=|website=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Broad City]]'', [[Hulu]]'s ''[[Difficult People]]'', MTV's ''Teachers' Lounge'', and, as himself, bartending on ''[[Watch What Happens Live]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817164820/https://sfsketchfest2017.sched.com/event/8wOr/trump-dump-with-anthony-atamanuik-and-guest-john-gemberling|title=SF Sketchfest 2017: Trump Dump with Anthony Atamanuik and gu...|author=|date=August 17, 2017|website=archive.org|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref>
