==''The President Show''== He is the creator and star of ''[[The President Show]]'', which premiered<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/president-show-anthony-atamanuik-mario-cantone-scaramucci-1202514133/|title=On ‘The President Show,’ Fake Donald Trump Builds a White House Staff|first=Brian|last=Steinberg|date=August 2, 2017|website=variety.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> on [[Comedy Central]] on April 27, 2017. On the show, he impersonates [[Donald Trump]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bravotv.com/watch-what-happens-live-with-andy-cohen/season-14/episode-85/videos/anthony-atamanuik-on-his-feud|title=Anthony Atamanuik on His Feud with Alec Baldwin|author=|date=May 11, 2017|website=bravotv.com|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/05/01/politics/donald-trump-the-president-show-comedy-central-anthony-atamanuik/index.html|title=If Donald Trump had a talk show|author=Chris Moody; Video by Alexander Rosen|date=|website=CNN|accessdate=August 17, 2017}}</ref> the [[President of the United States]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/03/arts/television/trump-talk-show-comedy-central-anthony-atamanuik-the-president-show.html|title=A Trump Talk Show, Courtesy of Comedy Central|first=Dave|last=Itzkoff|date=April 3, 2017|publisher=|accessdate=April 4, 2017|work=[[NYTimes.com]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2017/04/donald-trump-impression-gets-a-comedy-central-show/521718/|title='Donald Trump' Gets a Comedy Central Series|first=Megan|last=Garber|work=The Atlantic|accessdate=April 4, 2017}}</ref>
