{{COI|date=August 2013}} {{Infobox scientist <!-- Researchers category --> |region = [[Europe]] |era = [[21st-century researchers]] |color = #B0C4DE <!-- Image and caption --> |image = Javier-gil-sevillano.jpg |caption = Professor Javier Gil Sevillano (CEIT, 2010) <!-- Information --> |name = Javier Gil Sevillano |death_date = |death_place = |fields = Materials engineering |school_tradition = |main_interests = |known_for = Professor of materials engineering at [[Tecnun]] and head of Materials Research at [[CEIT]] |influences = |influenced = |residence = [[Donostia-San Sebastián]], Spain |citizenship = Spanish |nationality = |workplaces = |alma_mater = [[Katholieke Universiteit Leuven]] |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |awards = Mordica Memorial Award }}
'''Javier Gil Sevillano''' is the current professor of [[materials engineering]] at the [[Tecnun]] School of Engineering of the [[University of Navarra]] in Spain, and head of the Materials Department at [[CEIT]] Research Institute.<ref>http://www.ceit.es/index.php?option=com_personal&view=detalle&trbId=5&catId=91&prsId=0&Itemid=25&lang=es</ref>
A graduate in metallurgical engineering from the [[University of Navarra]], Professor Gil Sevillano obtained his PhD in at the [[Katholieke Universiteit Leuven]] in Belgium in 1978. The recipient of several awards,<ref>http://www.ceit.es/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=413:example-2&catid=21:news-a-events&Itemid=42&lang=es</ref> Spanish national newspaper ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'' has described him as "one of the leading scientists in materials research in the country".<ref>http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2010/05/03/paisvasco/1272875700.html</ref>
Sevillano's research has focused on the mechanical stress–strain response, structural evolution, texture development and fracture of materials undergoing large plastic strains. He has participated in more than 40 national and international research projects, has directed doctoral theses and is the author or co-author of about 130 scientific papers in refereed journals in the areas of materials science and technology.<ref>http://www.ceit.es/index.php?option=com_publicaciones&view=busqueda-resultados&Itemid=71&niu=00050364&lang=es</ref>
