{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox football biography | name= Sammy Bossut | image = Sammy Bossut.JPG | image_size = 280 | caption = Bossut in 2014 | fullname = Sammy Andre Bossut<ref>{{cite news | title = 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil: List of Players | url = http://www.fifadata.com/document/fwc/2014/pdf/fwc_2014_squadlists.pdf | publisher = FIFA | format = PDF | page = 4 | date = 11 June 2014 | accessdate = 10 July 2014}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|8|11|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tielt]], Belgium | height = {{height|m=1.87}} | currentclub = [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] | clubnumber = 1 | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = 1993-1997 | youthyears2 = 1997-1999 | youthyears3 = 1999-2003 | youthclubs1 = SC Oostrozebeke | youthclubs2 = [[K.S.V. Waregem|Waregem]] | youthclubs3 = [[Sporting West Harelbeke|Ingelmunster]] | years1 = 2003–2006 | years2 = 2006– | clubs1 = [[Sporting West Harelbeke]] | clubs2 = [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] | caps1 = 8 | caps2 = 334 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 0 |nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = | pcupdate = 21:32, 31 March 2017 (UTC) | ntupdate = }} '''Sammy Andre Bossut''' (born 11 August 1985) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] in the [[Belgian Pro League]].
He was a first team surprise in the [[UEFA Cup 2006–07|2006–07]] [[UEFA Cup]] return against [[Newcastle United]], in [[St James' Park, Newcastle|St James' Park]].
At the end of the [[Belgian First Division 2007–08|2007-08 season]], Zulte Waregem chose not to prolong the contract of [[Geert De Vlieger]], who was until then first choice goalkeeper. Bossut started the last matches of that season to gain more first team experience. Instead of signing a new goalkeeper, Bossut was awarded his spot in the starting eleven for the [[Belgian First Division 2008-09|2008–09 season]].
==International career== After [[Silvio Proto]] got injured, national manager [[Marc Wilmots]] called up Bossut as potential third goalkeeper for the [[Belgium national football team]] at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref name="Spza180514">{{cite news | title = Wilmots haalt Bossut bij WK-selectie na blessure Proto | publisher = [[Sporza]] | language = Dutch | date = 18 May 2014 | url = http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Rode_Duivels/140518_RD_bossut_opgeroepen | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140518211949/http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Rode_Duivels/140518_RD_bossut_opgeroepen | archivedate = 18 May 2014 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> Bossut played his first game with the national team against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] on 26 May 2014, but on 4 June FIFA ruled the match unofficial as Wilmots made 7 substitutions while only 6 are allowed in international friendlies.<ref name="HLN040614">{{cite web|url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/16076/De-Rode-Duivels/article/detail/1907260/2014/06/04/Debuut-Bossut-en-Januzaj-en-hattrick-Lukaku-zijn-ongeldig.dhtml |title=Debuut Bossut en Januzaj, én hattrick Lukaku zijn ongeldig|language=Dutch |publisher=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]] |date=4 June 2014 |accessdate=4 June 2014}}</ref>
